Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: When receiving a purchase order with multiple lines for the same item, the user scans the item to receive in the 'quantity' mode
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: The user is prompted for the correct order line to receive against. The user selects the specific order line that is being received and proceeds with the receiving process

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: When configured to display notes during receiving, the user scans or enters a purchase order that has notes populated at the header level
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: The user is displayed the note before the summary screen for the PO is shown

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: When configured to display notes during receiving, the user scans or enters a purchase order that has notes populated at the line level
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: The user is displayed the note after the line item is selected, and before the item is physically received

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: Receive overage against a PO where the overage quantity being received falls below the threshold set up at the item level, regardless of the set up in the workflow process
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: Able to receive the item and enter the overage quantity. The item setting over rides the workflow setting

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: Receive overage against a PO for an item that does not have the over receipt tolerance set at the item level. Enter a quantity that does not exceed the threshold set at the workflow process level
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: Able to receive the item and enter the overage quantity. The workflow setting is invoked

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: When prompted to scan the purchase order identifier to receive the purchase, the user scans or enters an invalid purchase order to receive against
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: The user is displayed an error that the identifier is invalid

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: When prompted to scan the purchase order identifier, the user scans a valid purchase order identifier that exists and has quantity left to receive
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: The user is taken to the screen to receive the items. The item summary screen is displayed

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: User partially receives the purchase order and hits the 'finish' button to temporarily exit the purchase order
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: The user is exited from the PO receiving screen. The PO goes to 'Receiving' status

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: User completes receiving the entire purchase order
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: The user is exited from the PO receiving screen. The PO goes to 'Received' status

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: User scans an item to begin the receiving process
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: The user is displayed the list of eligible POs for that item. The user selects the PO that the user needs to receive and begins the receiving process

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: User scans an item that has multiple packs in it's master data set up
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: The user is displayed a screen with all the packs for the item. The user selects the appropriate pack to receive

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: User receives against a non-each pack for a serial tracked item that requires serial capture at picking or packing
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: The receipt is completed at the non-each pack level. No attributes are captured

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: User receives against a non-each pack for an item that does not have item attribute capture requirements
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: The receipt is completed at the non-each pack level

Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 2: User receives a item tracked stock
Test Cases - Unit.Unnamed: 3: The respective attribute(s) are on the receipt line

GoNo-Go Decision.Unnamed: 3: To achieve a "YES" UAT onsite recommendation

To achieve a "YES" go-live recommendation, two things must occur:
(1) all items with a weight of 10 must have a % complete of at least 90%, and 
(2) the Total Percentage score at the bottom must have a % complete of at least 90%.  
Note,  even if these conditions are met, if the score is not 100%, there could be issues when going live.

Options.Open Item: Throw error/Remove New button for Order
Options.Resolution: Remove the Outbound order views completely from the Application menu. Customers can view the orders they have created by clicking into the orders from the Outbound Order Entry UI by either clicking into the order or by clicking the "i" icon to the right of the order
Options.Pros:
1. User is forced to use only the Sales Order Entry process, thus resolves the main issue
2. Order information can still be viewed
Options.Cons: If the user clicks the order link instead of "i" icon they are taken to this screen that has the "Proceed to Checkout" button. This button only shows more information about the order, nothing can be editted. We are looking to see if this can be greyed out

Options.Open Item: Different Outbound Order Entry views per Order Summary
Options.Resolution: This can only be done on a business unit level, not on an order attribute level
Templates can be created for each order summary with pre-filled information, and the user can copy this to create different types of orders
Data Exchange CSV uploads: Define template for both Outbound Orders and Fulfillment Orders.
Options.Pros: 1. Can control exactly which attributes we display for user to populate and import.  2. Clients do not need Create Order access and can still upload orders, no risk of clients editing orders.
Options.Cons: UI Sales Order Entry application not utilized
